metadata.name: Glacial Trail
metadata.description:
On the last day of my spontaneous Alaska trip, I decided to book a guided tour to the Matanuska Glacier. It's not often you get an opportunity to hike an iceberg!

Below freezing temperatures. Coupled with jaw-dropping views from every angle. 

Chilly, windy, and majestic. I felt the ice age remnant and its winter breeze pass through my whole body. Make the trek here if you ever find yourself in Anchorage, it's worth it.

Collector will receive a glass print of this otherworldly moment.
